flowRoot.flowPara: Yarnball is an online database service and visual editor that operates entirely on the basis of nodes and links. Unlike a typical database, there are no core data-types like numbers, booleans or strings. Instead, all data types, and any kind of structure, can be constructed from the basic building blocks - nodes and links.
Yarnball is a prototype for making data without data-types. Strings, arrays and objects do not exist built-in, but they can be made, along with anything, on the basis of Nodes and Links.
A surface is an infinite plane on which nodes can be placed, and links drawn between them.
Using nodes and links, any kind of structure can be constructed. Here are some basic examples.
